♫ I’m just someone, who isn’t that perfect ♫

9
00:00:26,120 --> 00:00:32,479
♫ But for you, I’m willing to give it all ♫

10
00:00:32,479 --> 00:00:36,720
♫ Whether you’d love me, or care about me or not ♫

11
00:00:36,720 --> 00:00:42,240
♫ That’s for you to decide, but as for me I’m… ♫

12
00:00:42,240 --> 00:00:44,760
♫ (Will be right here) not going anywhere ♫

13
00:00:44,760 --> 00:00:47,360
♫ (Hold my hand) stay by my side ♫

14
00:00:47,360 --> 00:00:52,280
♫ Just turn around and you’ll see ♫

15
00:00:52,640 --> 00:00:56,280
♫ You’ll always have me by your side ♫

16
00:00:56,280 --> 00:00:58,840
♫ In this marriage that our love will last forever♫

17
00:00:58,840 --> 00:01:04,280
♫ I promise I’ll give you all my heart♫

18
00:01:04,280 --> 00:01:07,120
♫ Remember when I said…♫

19
00:01:07,120 --> 00:01:12,200
♫ That I’ll take great care of you♫

20
00:01:12,200 --> 00:01:20,720
♫ I promise those words will always stay true♫

21
00:01:20,720 --> 00:01:23,240
[Marriage on Earth]

22
00:01:23,880 --> 00:01:26,280
I thought I’d never hear your voice again.

23
00:01:26,280 --> 00:01:28,240
Mr. Thipakorn finally comes round, Miss.

24
00:01:28,640 --> 00:01:31,039
I’m here, Dad. Please rest.

25
00:01:31,200 --> 00:01:33,000
Are you going to Chiang Mai again tomorrow?

26
00:01:33,240 --> 00:01:34,800
You can take a nap, Miss.

27
00:01:34,920 --> 00:01:36,360
I’ll wake you up when we get there.

28
00:01:36,640 --> 00:01:37,479
Miss Kaew!

29
00:01:37,600 --> 00:01:38,880
Surprised, aren’t you?

30
00:01:45,479 --> 00:01:45,880
Freeze!

31
00:01:45,880 --> 00:01:47,320
Did you fucking set me up?!

32
00:01:47,520 --> 00:01:49,759
We’ve found out long ago that Kaew works for you.

33
00:01:50,120 --> 00:01:53,680
Wasu and his father have escaped the police custody.

34
00:01:53,680 --> 00:01:55,560
Do you want to get arrested and thrown into jail?

35
00:01:55,560 --> 00:01:57,360
I’m going to ruin their lives.

36
00:01:58,200 --> 00:01:59,240
Let’s go!

37
00:01:59,240 --> 00:02:02,160
Let’s move! Go, go, go!

38
00:02:09,400 --> 00:02:11,120
Running for your life, aren’t  you?

39
00:02:11,840 --> 00:02:13,120
Run, Miss!

40
00:02:13,120 --> 00:02:14,240
Fuck off!

41
00:02:16,480 --> 00:02:18,640
Show her the gift I’ve prepared for her.

42
00:02:20,960 --> 00:02:22,200
- Walk!
- Kaew!

43
00:02:26,880 --> 00:02:28,079
Don’t hurt her!

44
00:02:28,079 --> 00:02:30,840
What? Are you afraid I’ll shoot her?

45
00:02:31,160 --> 00:02:33,520
Let her go. Leave her out of this.

46
00:02:35,200 --> 00:02:39,920
Fine. But I’ll let you choose. If you choose Rose,

47
00:02:40,880 --> 00:02:42,280
I’ll blow her head off.

48
00:02:44,920 --> 00:02:48,040
But if you choose this bitch, Rose will die.

49
00:02:49,200 --> 00:02:50,360
You’re insane!

50
00:02:50,400 --> 00:02:54,560
Choose! If you can’t, I’ll shoot you first!

51
00:02:54,840 --> 00:02:55,920
One!

52
00:02:57,120 --> 00:02:57,840
Two!

53
00:02:58,840 --> 00:03:00,800
Miss Din, Miss Rose! Run!

54
00:03:00,800 --> 00:03:04,200
- Kaew!
- Get off me!

55
00:03:04,520 --> 00:03:06,120
- Miss Din!
- Get off!

56
00:03:06,200 --> 00:03:08,240
Get off me!

57
00:03:18,840 --> 00:03:21,320
- Kaew!
- Miss Kaew!

58
00:03:23,880 --> 00:03:25,160
Shit! Police!

59
00:03:25,200 --> 00:03:26,960
Let's go! quick!

60
00:03:27,720 --> 00:03:28,760
Lom!

61
00:03:28,760 --> 00:03:29,720
Go check the victim!

62
00:03:31,160 --> 00:03:32,079
Kaew.

63
00:03:33,440 --> 00:03:34,800
Hang in there.

64
00:03:39,079 --> 00:03:39,880
Miss...

65
00:03:46,240 --> 00:03:47,440
I’m sorry.

66
00:03:49,320 --> 00:03:51,920
Don’t say anything right now.

67
00:03:52,960 --> 00:03:54,400
Fai, call the ambulance!

68
00:03:54,720 --> 00:03:55,520
Okay.

69
00:03:58,640 --> 00:04:01,040
Breathe, okay?

70
00:04:01,080 --> 00:04:02,560
Don’t worry, you’ll be all right.

71
00:04:34,240 --> 00:04:35,480
Give me the gun!

72
00:04:35,480 --> 00:04:36,800
That way, quick!

73
00:04:36,800 --> 00:04:37,920
- Go after them!
- Yes, sir!

74
00:04:47,240 --> 00:04:48,840
Put the gun down and turn yourself in.

75
00:04:49,040 --> 00:04:50,560
You might get to reduce your sentence.

76
00:05:20,160 --> 00:05:21,720
Miss Din! Miss!

77
00:05:22,560 --> 00:05:24,080
- Uncle Kla.
- How’s Kaew?

78
00:05:24,120 --> 00:05:25,480
She’s still in the OR.

79
00:05:32,000 --> 00:05:33,720
I’m really sorry, Miss.

80
00:05:34,240 --> 00:05:37,760
It’s my fault I didn’t raise her well enough…

81
00:05:38,640 --> 00:05:40,920
and let her cause you so much trouble…

82
00:05:41,680 --> 00:05:45,000
when you and your father have always been nothing but kind to us.

83
00:05:45,280 --> 00:05:46,360
I’m so sorry, Miss.

84
00:05:46,400 --> 00:05:48,640
That’s all right. It doesn’t matter at all.

85
00:05:48,960 --> 00:05:50,720
I forgive Kaew for everything.

86
00:05:50,720 --> 00:05:52,760
All I want right now is for her to be safe.

87
00:05:53,520 --> 00:05:54,760
It’s all right.

88
00:05:54,800 --> 00:05:55,840
Thank you so much, Miss.

89
00:05:56,080 --> 00:05:57,200
It’s okay.

90
00:05:58,960 --> 00:06:01,240
Don’t worry. It doesn’t matter at all.

91
00:06:03,600 --> 00:06:04,720
How’s she, Doctor?

92
00:06:05,160 --> 00:06:08,880
The patient has lost a lot of blood. I already removed the bullet.

93
00:06:08,880 --> 00:06:12,120
We’re keeping a close monitoring for possible internal bleeding.

94
00:06:12,640 --> 00:06:14,320
But we can’t say for certain yet.

95
00:06:14,320 --> 00:06:16,040
She must be kept under close monitoring for now.

96
00:06:17,520 --> 00:06:18,760
Thank you, Doctor.

97
00:06:23,680 --> 00:06:26,600
It’s okay now. It’s okay.

98
00:06:27,400 --> 00:06:28,880
Kaew will be all right.

99
00:06:28,880 --> 00:06:30,320
Please don’t worry.

100
00:06:30,360 --> 00:06:33,400
As for the hospital bills, I’ll take care of everything.

101
00:06:37,840 --> 00:06:39,920
Thank you, Miss.

102
00:06:41,080 --> 00:06:42,440
- She’ll be all right.
- Thank you very much.

103
00:06:44,600 --> 00:06:46,360
She’ll come back to us soon.

104
00:07:01,840 --> 00:07:03,800
Have you got your wound fixed?

105
00:07:05,240 --> 00:07:05,960
Yes, Miss.

106
00:07:09,040 --> 00:07:10,920
It’s just a little cut on the head.

107
00:07:11,560 --> 00:07:15,200
Please don’t worry, Miss. I’m pretty headstrong.

108
00:07:18,680 --> 00:07:20,200
I’m so sorry, Moddang.

109
00:07:21,280 --> 00:07:24,560
You got hurt because of me.

110
00:07:29,240 --> 00:07:31,240
It’s not your fault, Miss.

111
00:07:31,560 --> 00:07:33,040
It’s that bastard, Wasu.

112
00:07:34,120 --> 00:07:38,080
Please God, I hope he goes to hell right in the middle of the operation.

113
00:07:45,520 --> 00:07:49,720
You, Miss Kaew, and Din…

114
00:07:50,280 --> 00:07:52,440
all of you put your lives on the line because of me.

115
00:07:56,520 --> 00:07:59,960
Especially Miss Kaew, she’s still in a coma.

116
00:08:01,120 --> 00:08:04,440
It’s not your fault that Miss Kaew is like this.

117
00:08:05,440 --> 00:08:07,200
Please don’t blame yourself, Miss.

118
00:08:08,640 --> 00:08:12,680
But I’m the reason she ended up like this.

119
00:08:33,280 --> 00:08:35,159
Why don’t you go back and get some rest, Sis?

120
00:08:38,320 --> 00:08:42,080
Talk to her, Lom. I gave up. She wouldn't listen to me.

121
00:08:46,280 --> 00:08:49,280
I want to make sure Kaew is all right first.

122
00:08:50,960 --> 00:08:52,720
She’s still in a critical stage.

123
00:09:01,080 --> 00:09:03,440
By the way, how’s Wasu?

124
00:09:13,200 --> 00:09:14,280
Let me go!

125
00:09:14,840 --> 00:09:17,760
I said let me go! Just you wait! If I can get out,

126
00:09:18,240 --> 00:09:19,920
I’ll kill you all!

127
00:09:20,120 --> 00:09:23,080
The doctor said he won’t feel anything from the waist down.

128
00:09:23,400 --> 00:09:24,880
He won’t be able to walk again.

129
00:09:27,840 --> 00:09:31,040
Is there any update on Wasupol?

130
00:09:32,400 --> 00:09:35,560
The police found a body in the forest near the border.

131
00:09:36,120 --> 00:09:38,600
They’re trying to verify the identity.

132
00:09:40,080 --> 00:09:42,200
You think that body is him?

133
00:09:44,080 --> 00:09:49,400
Most likely. He probably got sacked once he was of no use.

134
00:09:49,400 --> 00:09:51,520
To stop him from squealing on the big boss.

135
00:09:59,200 --> 00:10:00,400
Let me go!

136
00:10:00,640 --> 00:10:01,960
I said let me go!

137
00:10:04,640 --> 00:10:06,560
Now, it’s all about the lawsuit.

138
00:10:06,800 --> 00:10:08,880
You might need to come to the police station more often during this time.

139
00:10:09,680 --> 00:10:11,000
Sure, no problem.

140
00:10:13,880 --> 00:10:17,760
What about you? Are you going to live here for good?

141
00:10:18,520 --> 00:10:22,040
I’m only staying to give her support. I’ll go home once everything is settled.

142
00:10:25,240 --> 00:10:27,560
Where’s Rose? I haven’t seen her around.

143
00:10:28,600 --> 00:10:30,760
Boss Rose went to see Uncle Thip.

144
00:10:30,760 --> 00:10:32,320
The doctor’s probably there to check on him by now.

145
00:10:39,280 --> 00:10:42,960
If possible, I’d like you to consider moving the patient to Bangkok for further treatment.

146
00:10:43,600 --> 00:10:48,440
They have more specialists and better equipment there.

147
00:10:48,840 --> 00:10:51,200
The patient will be able to recover faster that way.

148
00:10:52,440 --> 00:10:53,920
Move to Bangkok?

149
00:10:54,480 --> 00:10:57,680
Yes. Please give it a thought somehow.

150
00:11:00,160 --> 00:11:01,360
Get well soon.

151
00:11:07,760 --> 00:11:10,640
Do you want to go to Bangkok, Dad?

152
00:11:10,640 --> 00:11:12,760
So that you’ll recover faster.

153
00:11:13,720 --> 00:11:14,560
Yes.

154
00:11:16,320 --> 00:11:19,200
I want to try living like a city girl.

155
00:11:20,960 --> 00:11:23,640
I don’t remember saying anything about taking you with us.

156
00:11:24,440 --> 00:11:27,720
Please, Miss. Don’t leave me alone here.

157
00:11:28,080 --> 00:11:31,600
If you take me with you, I can help you look after Mr. Thipakorn.

158
00:11:31,600 --> 00:11:34,520
You already have someone to take care of you.

159
00:11:38,920 --> 00:11:40,360
It’s not Din’s job to do that.

160
00:11:42,600 --> 00:11:45,400
My dad has only left me under her care for a while.

161
00:11:50,240 --> 00:11:52,280
Now that he’s getting better,

162
00:11:56,960 --> 00:11:59,280
she’s no longer responsible for taking care of me.

163
00:12:36,720 --> 00:12:37,760
Thank you.

164
00:12:46,040 --> 00:12:48,480
What did the doctor say about Miss Kaew?

165
00:12:50,960 --> 00:12:52,080
She’s safe now.

166
00:13:03,960 --> 00:13:05,760
I’ll probably be busy for a while.

167
00:13:07,080 --> 00:13:11,640
I have to come to the hospital, go to the police station,

168
00:13:13,280 --> 00:13:16,280
and also handle Kaew’s and Uncle Kla’s works at the farm.

169
00:13:18,120 --> 00:13:20,600
I’ll ask Fai to keep you company in the meantime.

170
00:13:23,960 --> 00:13:26,720
Thank you. Please don’t worry about me.

171
00:13:32,600 --> 00:13:36,560
So, what did the doctor say about Uncle Thip?

172
00:13:41,280 --> 00:13:43,680
The doctor said he’s quite stable.

173
00:13:44,760 --> 00:13:46,040
There’s nothing to worry about.

174
00:13:51,280 --> 00:13:52,560
Let’s go home, shall we?

175
00:13:55,040 --> 00:13:55,800
Yes.

176
00:14:32,480 --> 00:14:34,600
Are you thinking about Mr. Thipakorn, Miss?

177
00:14:37,360 --> 00:14:39,360
Have you told Miss Din yet?

178
00:14:47,280 --> 00:14:48,960
I don’t know how to tell her.

179
00:14:52,880 --> 00:14:58,040
I’m afraid if I tell her, she might think that I’m leaving her.

180
00:15:00,520 --> 00:15:02,280
But on the other hand, it means

181
00:15:02,280 --> 00:15:06,000
we won’t have to be a burden to her anymore, Miss.

182
00:15:15,840 --> 00:15:17,880
I’ll try talking to her tomorrow.

183
00:15:53,600 --> 00:15:54,560
Din.

184
00:15:55,360 --> 00:15:56,360
Rose.

185
00:15:57,200 --> 00:16:00,040
I think you might be hungry, so I made you sandwiches.

186
00:16:01,080 --> 00:16:01,880
Thank you.

187
00:16:09,960 --> 00:16:11,200
Din.

188
00:16:11,800 --> 00:16:12,600
Yes?

189
00:16:18,120 --> 00:16:22,680
I…I need to talk to you about something.

190
00:16:24,240 --> 00:16:25,200
What is it?

191
00:16:26,680 --> 00:16:27,960
About my dad.

192
00:16:30,360 --> 00:16:31,160
Well…

193
00:16:35,040 --> 00:16:36,280
Yes, Uncle Kla?

194
00:16:38,320 --> 00:16:39,800
Kaew already came round?

195
00:16:40,160 --> 00:16:42,040
Okay, sure. I’ll be right there.

196
00:16:43,640 --> 00:16:44,920
Okay.

197
00:16:45,440 --> 00:16:49,600
Can we talk later, Rose? I have to go to the hospital.

198
00:16:49,800 --> 00:16:52,040
I’ll go with you. I want to visit Miss Kaew.

199
00:16:52,360 --> 00:16:53,240
Let’s go.

200
00:16:59,000 --> 00:17:00,400
Is this okay?

201
00:17:00,800 --> 00:17:02,160
- Yes.
- Okay.

202
00:17:02,960 --> 00:17:04,040
Oh, Miss Din.

203
00:17:07,920 --> 00:17:08,359
Kaew.

204
00:17:08,359 --> 00:17:11,920
Hold on, girl. The doctor said you shouldn’t move yet.

205
00:17:18,319 --> 00:17:23,680
Kaew, I’m so glad you’re safe.

206
00:17:24,680 --> 00:17:27,040
She’s worried sick about you.

207
00:17:34,400 --> 00:17:36,560
I’m sorry, Miss.

208
00:17:36,600 --> 00:17:41,120
No, Kaew. You don’t have to apologise.

209
00:17:46,360 --> 00:17:51,360
It’s me who has to say sorry. You got hurt because of me.

210
00:17:53,480 --> 00:17:54,840
It was my fault. I…

211
00:17:54,840 --> 00:17:56,240
No, Kaew.

212
00:17:58,600 --> 00:17:59,840
It wasn’t your fault.

213
00:18:04,680 --> 00:18:06,760
Wasu is the one to blame.

214
00:18:19,800 --> 00:18:21,160
You have to get well soon.

215
00:18:22,440 --> 00:18:23,240
Okay?

216
00:18:26,200 --> 00:18:27,200
Get well soon.

217
00:18:39,000 --> 00:18:42,280
Why are you crying?

218
00:18:46,480 --> 00:18:49,160
I want to move him to Bangkok for further treatment.

219
00:18:50,320 --> 00:18:51,520
That’s wonderful.

220
00:18:51,520 --> 00:18:53,440
Now that you've decided,

221
00:18:53,440 --> 00:18:56,920
I’ll tell them to proceed with the transferring documents.

222
00:18:59,600 --> 00:19:00,600
Thank you.

223
00:19:13,280 --> 00:19:17,960
Are you sure about this, my dear?

224
00:19:21,200 --> 00:19:25,800
Yes, Dad. I’ve troubled her much enough already.

225
00:19:53,920 --> 00:19:57,080
Rose, why do you want me to come see you here?

226
00:19:59,960 --> 00:20:03,240
I’m going to move Dad to Bangkok for further treatment.

227
00:20:04,240 --> 00:20:09,760
The doctor suggested that the technology and equipment there are better for his recovery.

228
00:20:12,680 --> 00:20:14,520
I'm here to say goodbye to you.

229
00:20:20,600 --> 00:20:21,400
Say goodbye?

230
00:20:23,840 --> 00:20:24,640
Yes.

231
00:20:26,120 --> 00:20:28,480
Thank you for taking care of me all this time.

232
00:20:31,600 --> 00:20:33,440
When are you leaving?

233
00:20:35,840 --> 00:20:37,000
As soon as I can.

234
00:20:41,800 --> 00:20:45,320
This is important. Why haven’t you told me earlier?

235
00:20:46,040 --> 00:20:48,200
You already have a lot on your plate.

236
00:20:48,600 --> 00:20:50,400
So, I didn’t tell you earlier.

237
00:20:53,480 --> 00:20:56,240
I’m also old enough to make my own decision.

238
00:21:02,600 --> 00:21:04,320
Then, I’ll go with you too.

239
00:21:04,600 --> 00:21:07,120
But can you please wait until I’ve settled everything here?

240
00:21:07,120 --> 00:21:10,400
And when will that be?

241
00:21:13,600 --> 00:21:16,240
We both have serious matters to focus on right now.

242
00:21:17,480 --> 00:21:19,920
You have a lot to take care of here,

243
00:21:19,920 --> 00:21:25,280
be it the farm or Miss Kaew who’s still recovering.

244
00:21:26,600 --> 00:21:31,040
I also want to focus on looking after my dad.

245
00:21:33,720 --> 00:21:36,640
We’re only going our separate way to do our job.

246
00:21:38,360 --> 00:21:42,640
It’s only temporary, not forever.

247
00:21:48,640 --> 00:21:54,240
Does this mean you'll come back to Chiang Rai?

248
00:21:55,880 --> 00:21:59,080
Yes, once Dad is fully recovered.

249
00:22:02,480 --> 00:22:03,640
I’ll be waiting then.

250
00:22:05,600 --> 00:22:07,440
I’ll wait for you to come back.

251
00:22:11,680 --> 00:22:18,880
While we’re apart, I want you to revisit your own heart and ask yourself…

252
00:22:21,400 --> 00:22:26,720
whether this love we have will last long enough to be true love.

253
00:22:28,360 --> 00:22:31,200
Or is it merely just a result of a fake marriage?

254
00:22:35,720 --> 00:22:38,400
I’ll take this time to reflect on my own heart too.

255
00:23:06,240 --> 00:23:08,600
If you’re sure I’m still that person in your heart,

256
00:23:10,760 --> 00:23:16,120
then you can return this ring to me…

257
00:23:18,000 --> 00:23:20,160
when we see each other again.

258
00:23:26,040 --> 00:23:29,720
♫Have you ever loved me?♫

259
00:23:29,720 --> 00:23:33,440
♫Please let me know♫

260
00:23:33,440 --> 00:23:39,960
♫If those hugs you gave me meant anything at all♫

261
00:23:39,960 --> 00:23:47,200
♫I don’t want to imagine it alone. Do you also feel the same?♫

262
00:23:47,200 --> 00:23:52,920
♫Forget about that promise and tell me honestly♫

263
00:23:52,920 --> 00:23:57,600
♫If you’ve ever loved me at all♫

264
00:24:00,240 --> 00:24:04,000
♫Have you ever loved me?♫

265
00:24:04,000 --> 00:24:07,760
♫Please let me know♫

266
00:24:07,760 --> 00:24:14,280
♫If those hugs you gave me meant anything at all♫

267
00:24:14,280 --> 00:24:21,520
♫I don’t want to imagine it alone. Do you also feel the same?♫

268
00:24:21,520 --> 00:24:27,160
♫Forget about that promise and tell me honestly♫

269
00:24:27,160 --> 00:24:30,960
♫If you’ve ever loved me at all♫

270
00:25:43,040 --> 00:25:44,800
Let’s go inside, Dad.

271
00:25:45,600 --> 00:25:46,480
Okay.

272
00:25:49,120 --> 00:25:51,080
The house looks lovely.

273
00:26:16,360 --> 00:26:20,000
Hello. My father has an appointment with the doctor today.

274
00:26:20,120 --> 00:26:22,680
Yes, Miss. Please come this way for a BP check.

275
00:26:22,680 --> 00:26:23,640
Let's go, Dad.

276
00:26:26,040 --> 00:26:30,880
[Neurosurgical, Brain, and Spinal Cord Department]

277
00:27:58,560 --> 00:28:01,880
Dad and I are here to say goodbye to you. We’re going back to Chiang Mai.

278
00:28:09,960 --> 00:28:13,880
Have you thought about what you’d do there?

279
00:28:17,520 --> 00:28:20,640
I’ll probably take a small job once I’m fully recovered.

280
00:28:22,240 --> 00:28:25,040
As for me, I’m going to retire.

281
00:28:25,040 --> 00:28:28,200
Maybe grow some vegetables for sale in our garden.

282
00:28:33,640 --> 00:28:38,240
Since you two have decided, I wouldn’t say otherwise.

283
00:28:40,240 --> 00:28:44,560
I wish you both good luck for the new beginning in life.

284
00:28:50,200 --> 00:28:51,880
Thank you so much, Miss.

285
00:28:52,320 --> 00:28:54,240
We’ll always be indebted to you.

286
00:28:54,240 --> 00:28:57,440
Kaew and I will never forget the kindness you and your father have given us.

287
00:29:02,360 --> 00:29:04,480
Thank you for everything, Miss.

288
00:29:06,000 --> 00:29:07,800
Please tell Miss Rose I’m sorry.

289
00:29:18,360 --> 00:29:20,000
Don’t worry about that.

290
00:29:21,480 --> 00:29:23,240
Going back to Chiang Mai,

291
00:29:23,240 --> 00:29:25,880
if you ever need anything, you can always let me know.

292
00:29:31,440 --> 00:29:36,040
Saen Rak farm will always be your home.

293
00:29:51,920 --> 00:29:53,280
Good luck.

294
00:29:54,040 --> 00:29:55,040
Goodbye, Miss.

295
00:30:23,040 --> 00:30:25,080
Aww, there you are.

296
00:30:28,360 --> 00:30:31,480
Looking completely hopeless just like Lom said.

297
00:30:33,120 --> 00:30:34,920
Why didn’t you tell me you’d come?

298
00:30:38,600 --> 00:30:41,600
I want to see the gloomy face of someone who got dumped.

299
00:30:50,320 --> 00:30:55,680
If you love her and miss her so much that you have to come look at her flowers every day,

300
00:30:55,680 --> 00:30:57,600
why don’t you just go and see her?

301
00:31:01,320 --> 00:31:05,920
How? I don’t even know where she is right now.

302
00:31:10,000 --> 00:31:13,920
Lom has sniffed around and managed to find out where Boss Rose lives.

303
00:32:14,480 --> 00:32:16,440
Since we came to live here,

304
00:32:17,200 --> 00:32:20,520
I haven’t seen her smiling cheerfully like she used to again.

305
00:32:21,520 --> 00:32:23,680
She must have missed Miss Din so bad.

306
00:32:26,440 --> 00:32:27,800
Rose missess Din?

307
00:32:30,400 --> 00:32:31,200
Yes.

308
00:32:40,880 --> 00:32:42,520
While I was unconscious,

309
00:32:44,760 --> 00:32:48,080
what happened between Rose and Din?

310
00:32:50,200 --> 00:32:51,680
Tell me everything.

311
00:32:53,000 --> 00:32:54,280
Yes.

312
00:33:04,040 --> 00:33:05,560
Hold on, Dad.

313
00:33:13,360 --> 00:33:15,560
I’ll go get you the medicine.

314
00:33:15,920 --> 00:33:17,360
I’ll be right back.

315
00:33:20,280 --> 00:33:21,360
Wait, Rose.

316
00:33:25,920 --> 00:33:29,120
I need to talk to you about something. It’s about Din.

317
00:33:35,160 --> 00:33:36,960
Did you and her fight?

318
00:33:40,840 --> 00:33:42,600
Are you two having a row?

319
00:33:46,040 --> 00:33:46,920
No, Dad.

320
00:33:48,640 --> 00:33:49,480
Are you sure?

321
00:33:51,600 --> 00:33:52,400
Yes.

322
00:33:56,000 --> 00:33:58,760
Then, why are you not getting in touch with her?

323
00:34:12,520 --> 00:34:15,520
I want to give her time to deal with her own life.

324
00:34:20,679 --> 00:34:25,639
Besides, that promise she gave you before the accident…

325
00:34:27,320 --> 00:34:29,040
It’s over now.

326
00:34:33,280 --> 00:34:34,600
Do you love her?

327
00:34:43,960 --> 00:34:44,679
Yes.

328
00:34:47,400 --> 00:34:48,920
I love her.

329
00:34:56,560 --> 00:35:01,800
If that’s so, are you going to let it end just like this?

330
00:35:33,320 --> 00:35:38,800
[Thipakorn] : If that’s so, are you going to let it end just like this?

331
00:36:04,600 --> 00:36:06,200
I miss you so much, Din.

332
00:36:33,280 --> 00:36:34,720
[Rose] : While we’re apart,

333
00:36:36,240 --> 00:36:38,600
I want you to revisit your own heart and ask yourself…

334
00:36:41,040 --> 00:36:46,480
whether this love we have will last long enough to be true love.

335
00:36:57,120 --> 00:36:58,000
[Moddang] : Is it good?

336
00:36:58,480 --> 00:36:59,440
[Thipakorn] : Fantastic.

337
00:37:05,040 --> 00:37:07,040
Rose, come eat with me, dear.

338
00:37:15,600 --> 00:37:17,400
Why are there so many northern dishes?

339
00:37:19,800 --> 00:37:22,240
Oh, Moddang’s prepared everything.

340
00:37:22,280 --> 00:37:27,080
I bought them, Miss. I won a lotto yesterday.

341
00:37:28,640 --> 00:37:29,720
A lotto?

342
00:37:33,160 --> 00:37:35,160
But it wasn’t a lottery day yesterday.

343
00:37:35,920 --> 00:37:37,960
I only got to check it yesterday.

344
00:37:41,880 --> 00:37:42,960
Come, dear.

345
00:37:42,960 --> 00:37:46,200
Hurry and finish your meal, or I’ll be late for the doctor’s appointment.

346
00:37:46,200 --> 00:37:49,040
They are all delicious.

347
00:37:49,080 --> 00:37:49,960
Okay.

348
00:37:55,160 --> 00:37:56,480
Try them, Miss.

349
00:37:56,720 --> 00:37:59,160
Everything is so tasty.

350
00:38:02,680 --> 00:38:04,680
Here, isn’t this your favourite?

351
00:38:08,760 --> 00:38:10,280
Try it.

352
00:38:16,800 --> 00:38:18,280
Hurry up and eat.

353
00:38:19,680 --> 00:38:23,320
Try the pork scratchings too. They’re really good.

354
00:38:29,800 --> 00:38:31,320
Whose car is this, Dad?

355
00:38:31,960 --> 00:38:34,280
Oh, it’s my friend’s.

356
00:38:34,280 --> 00:38:38,400
Since we have to be in Bangkok for a while, she said we can use her car while we’re here.

357
00:38:38,400 --> 00:38:40,360
She’s worried I’ll have a hard time.

358
00:38:45,760 --> 00:38:47,200
Be careful, Dad.

359
00:38:58,560 --> 00:38:59,960
All right there.

360
00:39:07,240 --> 00:39:08,720
Have a safe trip.

361
00:39:36,600 --> 00:39:37,400
Are they gone?

362
00:39:37,600 --> 00:39:38,400
Yes.

363
00:39:39,640 --> 00:39:40,760
Thanks a lot, Mod....

364
00:39:40,920 --> 00:39:44,120
How long are you going to keep playing hide-and-seek with Miss Rose like this?

365
00:39:45,880 --> 00:39:47,760
Why can’t you two just talk and clear it up?

366
00:39:47,760 --> 00:39:49,960
You both clearly miss each other so much.

367
00:39:51,080 --> 00:39:54,760
Well, Rose told me she wanted to focus on Uncle Thip.

368
00:39:55,040 --> 00:39:57,520
So, I’m giving her time and space to do as she will.

369
00:39:57,680 --> 00:40:00,040
Wow, what a gentlewoman.

370
00:40:00,320 --> 00:40:01,960
And you also want to give her time.

371
00:40:01,960 --> 00:40:03,920
Miss Rose wants to give you time.

372
00:40:04,840 --> 00:40:06,520
It’s such a waste of time, Miss!

373
00:40:25,920 --> 00:40:29,400
You bought so much food and also brought some flowers,

374
00:40:29,400 --> 00:40:32,000
aren’t you afraid she’d find out?

375
00:40:35,080 --> 00:40:38,280
Haven’t you told her already that you won a lotto?

376
00:40:39,280 --> 00:40:41,680
I can come to Bangkok for only two days a week.

377
00:40:42,640 --> 00:40:44,760
I want to do whatever I can for her.

378
00:40:45,640 --> 00:40:48,360
But I can’t win a lotto every week, Miss.

379
00:40:51,840 --> 00:40:52,920
Then…

380
00:40:54,760 --> 00:40:57,440
just tell her a friend of Uncle Thip came by to visit.

381
00:41:03,560 --> 00:41:06,040
Holy smokes! Why are they back so early?

382
00:41:08,200 --> 00:41:10,120
I have to hide!

383
00:41:10,120 --> 00:41:12,640
Not there, Miss! Go under the table!

384
00:41:12,640 --> 00:41:14,160
Get in there! Quick!

385
00:41:20,480 --> 00:41:22,560
Why are you back so early today?

386
00:41:23,280 --> 00:41:25,800
The queue at the hospital is quite short.

387
00:41:26,120 --> 00:41:26,920
I see.

388
00:41:30,680 --> 00:41:34,120
What do we have for lunch? I’m starving.

389
00:41:35,840 --> 00:41:37,360
Just a second, Dad.

390
00:41:44,440 --> 00:41:46,240
Who bought all this food?

391
00:41:47,400 --> 00:41:49,560
My relative has come to Bangkok…

392
00:41:49,800 --> 00:41:52,720
so she just dropped by and even brought me food.

393
00:42:00,320 --> 00:42:01,320
What about the flowers?

394
00:42:02,560 --> 00:42:12,440
I also asked her to pick some flowers from our farm for you, Miss.

395
00:42:16,480 --> 00:42:19,200
Where’s she then? Your relative.

396
00:42:19,840 --> 00:42:20,800
She left.

397
00:42:44,400 --> 00:42:46,440
What is it? A mosquito?

398
00:42:46,440 --> 00:42:47,760
Yes, it bit me.

399
00:42:48,640 --> 00:42:50,080
Use the mosquito spray then.

400
00:43:45,760 --> 00:43:47,480
Hello, Rose.

401
00:44:04,280 --> 00:44:06,240
While you’re away,

402
00:44:07,760 --> 00:44:10,880
I stop by your farm to tend to the flowers every day.

403
00:44:12,440 --> 00:44:16,760
All of them are now blooming. Not a single one is withering.

404
00:44:19,000 --> 00:44:21,400
You sure have lots of free time, huh?

405
00:44:22,320 --> 00:44:26,160
Yes, I have plenty of time now.

406
00:44:26,160 --> 00:44:31,400
After Wasu’s case is over, I’ve wrapped up all the unfinished works.

407
00:44:32,840 --> 00:44:35,080
Also, Kaew and Uncle Kla decided to quit…

408
00:44:35,080 --> 00:44:37,040
and move back to Chiang Mai.

409
00:44:37,040 --> 00:44:40,560
So, I hired a new batch of workers.

410
00:44:40,880 --> 00:44:42,560
That’s why I have a lot of free time now.

411
00:44:44,280 --> 00:44:45,080
I see.

412
00:45:05,080 --> 00:45:10,600
From now on, I’ll drive down from Chiang Rai to see you every weekend.

413
00:45:11,080 --> 00:45:13,840
I’ll do that until you and Uncle Thip return to the farm.

414
00:45:16,120 --> 00:45:17,920
Why would you do that?

415
00:45:19,080 --> 00:45:21,800
Driving a long way back and forth is dangerous.

416
00:45:23,400 --> 00:45:24,320
Not a problem at all.

417
00:45:25,160 --> 00:45:27,240
For me, Bangkok or Chiang Rai is only a few minutes away.

418
00:45:28,080 --> 00:45:30,320
True love conquers miles.

419
00:45:33,120 --> 00:45:36,560
I’ll come to say ‘I love you’ in person every Saturday.

420
00:45:40,200 --> 00:45:43,760
You don’t have to do that.

421
00:45:50,240 --> 00:45:51,200
Why?

422
00:45:51,480 --> 00:45:54,480
Is it because you don't want to see me anymore?

423
00:45:56,360 --> 00:45:59,880
It’s not like that. I just don’t want you to come all the way here for nothing.

424
00:46:05,920 --> 00:46:06,720
What?

425
00:46:14,760 --> 00:46:17,320
The doctor said Dad can go back to Chiang Rai.

426
00:46:20,680 --> 00:46:24,840
If you come here next week, you won’t find anyone here…

427
00:46:24,840 --> 00:46:26,720
but an empty house.

428
00:46:27,680 --> 00:46:31,040
Does this mean you’re going back to Chiang Rai too?

429
00:46:32,240 --> 00:46:35,920
Of course, my home is in Chiang Rai.

430
00:46:36,280 --> 00:46:38,840
Where else could I go if not there?

431
00:47:09,480 --> 00:47:10,720
I miss you.

432
00:47:11,560 --> 00:47:12,600
I miss you too.

433
00:47:35,560 --> 00:47:41,000
Thank you for always taking care of Rose and my farm all this time. I really appreciate it.

434
00:47:43,800 --> 00:47:48,120
It’s really nothing, Uncle. You’ve taken good care of me after my dad passed away too.

435
00:47:49,400 --> 00:47:52,080
You’re like a father to me.

436
00:47:55,840 --> 00:47:57,960
Do you want me to be your father-in-law too?

437
00:48:01,680 --> 00:48:02,480
Dad!

438
00:48:08,480 --> 00:48:10,840
Honestly, I’m fine with that.

439
00:48:12,280 --> 00:48:15,400
Because you two already got married once, didn’t you?

440
00:48:23,000 --> 00:48:26,680
It was a fake marriage, Dad.

441
00:48:30,680 --> 00:48:33,320
Then, why don’t you get married for real?

442
00:48:34,760 --> 00:48:37,240
I’ll be there to witness your marriage this time.

443
00:48:37,520 --> 00:48:39,880
I wasn't there when you got married last time.

444
00:48:42,880 --> 00:48:44,360
Daddy.

445
00:48:44,800 --> 00:48:45,600
Yes?

446
00:48:45,640 --> 00:48:48,400
I haven’t agreed to go back to her yet.

447
00:48:50,960 --> 00:48:53,000
Can’t you let me play hard to get for a bit?

448
00:48:56,280 --> 00:48:58,360
Can you still do that?

449
00:48:58,400 --> 00:48:59,840
Aren’t you protective of your daughter at all?

450
00:49:01,520 --> 00:49:03,080
I am. I love you so much too.

451
00:49:03,400 --> 00:49:07,640
But earlier, Rose gave me a peck on the cheek first.

452
00:49:09,080 --> 00:49:10,560
Huh? Really?

453
00:49:17,680 --> 00:49:20,000
- Din!
- Come on. I don’t think that’s playing hard to get.

454
00:49:20,000 --> 00:49:21,200
Don’t be a snitch!

455
00:49:25,880 --> 00:49:26,920
I’m so embarrassed.

456
00:49:41,400 --> 00:49:42,840
Careful, Dad.

457
00:49:47,640 --> 00:49:48,680
Nice weather, isn’t it?

458
00:49:49,240 --> 00:49:50,600
Absolutely.

459
00:49:54,840 --> 00:49:56,360
Please take it easy.

460
00:50:14,440 --> 00:50:16,680
Now that we’re back in Chiang Rai,

461
00:50:16,680 --> 00:50:21,880
does this mean you’re going to reconcile with Din?

462
00:50:25,920 --> 00:50:29,200
Did she tell you to ask me that?

463
00:50:33,400 --> 00:50:37,960
Listen, sweetie. It’s not good for lovers…

464
00:50:39,080 --> 00:50:43,360
to stay estranged for too long. It’s such a waste of time.

465
00:50:44,040 --> 00:50:48,680
If I were you, I would’ve moved to Saen Rak farm by now.

466
00:50:51,200 --> 00:50:54,200
Dad! I’m a girl somehow.

467
00:50:54,920 --> 00:50:57,840
And she still hasn’t proposed to me yet.

468
00:50:58,480 --> 00:51:01,760
How can I move in with her?

469
00:51:03,720 --> 00:51:10,920
Does this mean you’re waiting for her to propose to you?

470
00:51:10,920 --> 00:51:12,040
Right?

471
00:51:12,520 --> 00:51:13,640
Dad!

472
00:51:15,840 --> 00:51:17,480
Miss Rose! Miss!

473
00:51:18,240 --> 00:51:19,480
We’ve got a problem!

474
00:51:20,120 --> 00:51:22,320
Someone has trespassed on our farm!

475
00:51:23,680 --> 00:51:24,840
Where are they now?

476
00:51:24,880 --> 00:51:26,080
Please follow me, Miss.

477
00:51:28,560 --> 00:51:30,560
I’ll be right back, Dad.

478
00:51:30,760 --> 00:51:31,840
Go on then.

479
00:51:32,280 --> 00:51:33,520
Let’s go, Miss.

480
00:51:33,560 --> 00:51:34,680
Please be careful.

481
00:51:45,080 --> 00:51:46,520
This way, Miss!

482
00:51:58,200 --> 00:51:59,280
Moddang!

483
00:52:01,120 --> 00:52:02,240
Moddang!

484
00:52:43,760 --> 00:52:47,160
Din, where are you?

485
00:52:49,840 --> 00:52:54,200
Show yourself. I know it’s you.

486
00:53:06,760 --> 00:53:09,760
Or do I have to cry like that time when I was a kid?

487
00:53:10,200 --> 00:53:12,320
So that you’d come out.

488
00:53:15,680 --> 00:53:16,640
I’m here.

489
00:53:35,040 --> 00:53:36,600
What are you playing?

490
00:53:48,520 --> 00:53:52,600
Do you still remember what this place means?

491
00:53:57,880 --> 00:54:04,800
This place…is where we first met when I was still little.

492
00:54:06,520 --> 00:54:12,240
I came here with my dad, and saw you crying here.

493
00:54:20,360 --> 00:54:21,640
Rose,

494
00:54:23,040 --> 00:54:26,840
our bond isn’t built overnight or in just two months.

495
00:54:30,280 --> 00:54:32,400
It took us 20 years.

496
00:54:34,360 --> 00:54:41,120
Can you give me a chance to prove that 20 years from now or even longer than that,

497
00:54:42,800 --> 00:54:47,480
I’ll love only you…and it’ll never change.

498
00:55:27,120 --> 00:55:31,480
Rose, please marry me.

499
00:55:36,880 --> 00:55:41,600
Let’s make it real this time, not just a fake marriage like last time.

500
00:55:43,040 --> 00:55:48,200
Let’s get married because we truly love each other…from the bottom of our hearts.

501
00:55:50,440 --> 00:55:53,360
♫ (Will be right here) not going anywhere ♫

502
00:55:53,360 --> 00:55:55,840
♫ (Hold my hand) stay by my side ♫

503
00:55:55,840 --> 00:56:00,880
♫ Just turn around and you’ll see ♫

504
00:56:01,200 --> 00:56:04,320
Yes, I’ll marry you.
♫ You’ll always have me by your side ♫

505
00:56:04,320 --> 00:56:07,280
Yes, I’ll marry you.
♫In this marriage that our love will last forever♫

506
00:56:07,320 --> 00:56:12,720
♫ I promise I’ll give you all my heart♫

507
00:56:12,720 --> 00:56:15,400
♫ Remember when I said…♫

508
00:56:15,400 --> 00:56:20,560
♫ That I’ll take great care of you♫

509
00:56:20,640 --> 00:56:27,240
♫ I promise those words will always stay true♫

510
00:56:27,240 --> 00:56:33,160
♫ ‘Cause you are my love. Always remember that ♫

511
00:56:33,160 --> 00:56:37,880
♫ No matter how much time has passed, you’ll always be in my heart ♫

512
00:56:37,880 --> 00:56:44,200
♫ From now on, we’ll always have each other ♫

513
00:56:44,200 --> 00:56:52,200
♫ All my life, I’ll give it to you and will love only you forever ♫

514
00:58:58,040 --> 00:58:59,760
Please look after her for me.

515
00:59:03,320 --> 00:59:08,600
But this time, it won’t be temporary.

516
00:59:12,040 --> 00:59:14,520
